If a character is neither upper case nor lowercase, you should just take it as is. Also, don&#39;t use a `String` to accumulate your output - this is what `StringBuilder`s are for:

    public static String toggleString(String sentence) {
        StringBuilder toggled = new StringBuilder(sentence.length());
        for (char letter : sentence.toCharArray()) {
            if(Character.isUpperCase(letter)) {
                letter = Character.toLowerCase(letter);
            } else if(Character.isLowerCase(letter)) {
                letter = Character.toUpperCase(letter);
            }

            toggled.append(letter);

        }
        return toggled.toString();
    }

